reviews.text: I wouldn't describe the food as bad, but it isn't really worth the price.

If you want to revisit Hong Kong diner-style western food from the 60s and 70s, then look no further than a Salsbury Steak, Russian Borscht and sweet Milk Tea.  This is 'fusion' before fusion was even a thing.  I wouldn't say it good, but does bring back my childhood nostalgia.  Don't forget to finish your meal with a cup of cubed jello topped with Carnation condensed milk.
Good Hong Kong style Milk Tea

reviews.text: 走中高檔茶餐廳路線，味道及格，價錢一般，可以一試
食咗鮮茄牛脷飯 價錢較貴 不過牛脷極多 所以性價比不錯
午餐同夜餐價錢貴都係早餐平 呀 來來去去得嗰幾款食物。
午膳時段，有很多人，單拖一人，不去為皆
方便、快捷、好味、份量足。倘若餐牌增加款式，如快餐店的百搭餐類。洗手間搞清潔些，服務人員加多些少笑容將近乎完美。
